deck: Chretian fought in the crusades for adventure and profit and bid Covenant to do the same.
description:
History

One night, Muslim warriors destroyed Covenant’s camp while he slept. Chretien, who sold his allies out for profit, had tipped off the Muslims. Covenant was killed, and as he died, he felt at peace knowing that he would be welcomed into Heaven, but he was wrong. Chretien returned home as a rich man, but his wealth and debauchery could not numb the guilt he felt for his past sins. As time went on, he slowly slipped into madness, wandering about the countryside seeing ghosts and haunted by his sins. Chretien suffered even after his death. Now, he roams the world telling his history.
name: Chretien DuSang De La Croix

deck: DuBlanc was the wicked enforcer of taxes in Rhyll, often killing or maiming those who could not pay.
description:
History

The handsome but tremendously vain captain at arms for Baron Rivalen. DuBlanc was the wicked enforcer of taxes in Rhyll, often killing or maiming those who could not pay.

In a fight with Covenant, Dublanc was hideously scarred and began to wear a mystical horned mask given to him by the evil Sisters of the Morrigan. Scarred in both body and pride, DuBlanc became even more vicious and vowed revenge upon Covenant.

He followed Covenant across the countryside until they had their final confrontation in France. Covenant warned DuBlanc to abandon his petty quest for revenge and shrugged him off after removing DuBlanc's hand in battle.
name: Guy DuBlanc

volume_credits.name: Spawn: The Dark Ages The Complete Collection

deck: An angel of the Seraphic Huntress class.
description:
History

Immaculata hunted hellspawn for centuries until a battle with a particularly formidable Spawn in the ancient city of Illium.

Near defeat, Immaculata summoned all strength she had left and annihilated the hellspawn. Unfortunately, she also destroyed the entire city, killing untold thousands of innocent people. Fraught with grief and guilt, Immaculata quit hunting and lived a life of devotion on Earth.

She eventually settled in France during the Dark Ages as a sister in the Abbey of Sainte Barbe. When the hellspawn Covenant appeared at her doorstep, she felt called to her duty once again. In her confrontation with Covenant, however, she decided once and for all to renounce her mantel and her calling.

Soon after, while rescuing a baby from the burning abbey, Immaculata was murdered by Cogliostro. Cogliostro kept her ceremonial headdress as a trophy and eventually placed it in his Archives of the Hellspawn. When Spawn was given a tour of the archives, the headdress and its ribbons attacked Spawn - they had a bit of life in them yet.
name: Sister Immaculata

volume_credits.name: Spawn: The Dark Ages The Complete Collection

deck: A young unwed mother.

Along with her boyfriend Reynard, was accosted in the forest for a group of burglars. Covenant happened by and rescued them, after which he escorted them to the nearby Abbey of Sainte Barbe so Marie could give birth.

Soon after Marie and Reynard had their little girl, the Abbey was set ablaze by Guy DuBlanc. Marie did not escape the fire, but her baby and Reynard did thanks to the angel Immaculata, for whom the baby girl was named.

deck: A young peasant that left home with his girlfriend Marie after she became pregnant.
description:
Story

While he was traveling through a forest with the mother of his child, both were attacked by bandits but with luck, were rescued by Covenant.

The hellspawn escorted the couple to a nearby abbey so Marie could give birth safely. Soon after, Marie and Reynard had their little girl, the abbey was set ablaze by Guy DuBlanc.

Marie did not escape the fire, but her baby and Reynard did thanks to the angel Immaculata, for whom the baby girl was named.

Reynard, stricken with grief, left little Immaculata in the care of the convent and ventured off, promising to return one day.
name: Reynard

deck: The mysterious human spirit that brings Robbie Reyes back to life and inhabits his body, granting Robbie the powers of the All-New Ghost Rider.
description:
Origin

Creation

Robbie Reyes was co-created by Felipe Smith. He made his first appearance in All-New Ghost Rider #1, May 26, 2014.

Major Story Arcs

Engines of Vengeance

Legend

Great Power

Powers

Spirit of Eli Morrow

A Russian mobster, a sadistic serial killer, a devoted Satanist... and Robbie's uncle. Eli W. Morrow escaped eternal damnation through Satanic rituals to once again walk among the living and resume his killing spree. Embedded in Robbie’s psyche, Eli feeds off his anger and despair, and in exchange gives Robbie the great power to change into the All-New Ghost Rider (All-New Ghost Rider #9 - Legend). A Hellish monster similar to a Ghost Rider with supernatural strength, speed, durability, regeneration, unlimited stamina and spewing Hellfire generation. There has never been a human spirit on human spirit Rider before, as such there are unique powers and anomolies found in Robbie’s bond unlike previous Riders. The ornate facial scarring, the discoloration in Robbie’s right eye, all of which respond directly to his emotional state. However, if Robbie gives in to his despair, and lets his negative feelings dominate, Eli Morrow can take over completely. A change displayed in pale skin and a fiery glow in both eyes (All-New Ghost Rider #8). Because Robbie is the first Rider of his kind, it is unknown how his powers will evolve, but Eli claims they get stronger everyday (All-New Ghost Rider #4 - Engines of Vengeance). Together their powers could be limitless.

Bond

Through the process of bringing a freshly dead, compatible spirit back to life, the Spirit of Eli Morrow could inhabit and empower unassuming hosts at will. Now however, that Robbie Reyes has avenged Eli Morrow's death, their souls are eternally bonded. Eli can no longer jump from host to host and Robbie can never be rid of Eli Morrow's presence (All-New Ghost Rider #12).

Intermediate Transformation

Unlike a traditional Ghost Rider, Eli Morrow can give Robbie access to a fraction of the All-New Ghost Rider's strength, speed, and durability. When this transformation occurs Robbie's ornate facial scarring will illuminate and he may or may not exhibit Hellfire breath or steam (All-New Ghost Rider #7).

Other Media

Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.

On Marvel's Agents of SHIELD, Eli is in prison for attempted manslaughter. It appears he's a "good man that did a bad thing." Eli raised Robbie and his brother Gabe. His involvement in the experiments involving a book called the Darkhold are revealed in the episode "The Good Samaritan" He is played by José Zúñiga.

Origin

Creation

Ragyo Kiryuin (鬼龍院 羅暁, Kiryūin Ragyō) is the main antagonist of the Kill la Kill anime series that was produced by Trigger. It's directed by Hiroyuki Imaishi and written by Kazuki Nakashima. The character design was done by Sushio.

A tie-in manga series illustrated by Ryou Akizuki began on October 4, 2013 in Kadokawa Shoten's Young Ace magazine.

Other Media

Anime

Kill la Kill (2013)

Kill la Kill (キルラキル Kiru ra Kiru) is the first original anime production created by Trigger, which was founded by two former Gainax employees in 2011. The series is directed by Hiroyuki Imaishi, Trigger co-founder; and written by Kazuki Nakashima. The first episode aired on October 3, 2010.

Ragyo's first anime appearance was in Kill la Kill - Episode 6 "Don't Toy Me on a Whim ", which aired on November 7, 2013. Her character in the Japanese series was voiced by Romi Paku.
name: Ragyo Kiryuin
